# Vibe Coding Entry

If the user says "vibe coding", asks to follow a three-phase workflow, or references `Docs/` artifacts:

1. Load and follow the project skill **vibe-coding-workflow** (`.cursor/skills/vibe-coding-workflow/SKILL.md`).
2. Enforce phase gates: Clarify + **user-confirmed landing details** before Plan, Plan before Implement.
3. During implementation, do not allow silent deviations from `{TaskName}_Plan.md`; apply the deviation protocol first. Before task close: **build + smoke-run** (skill § Phase 3) unless documented N/A — use test CLI from **`vulkan-smoke-test.mdc`** / **`Docs/CLI.md`** (prefer `--no-validation --smoke-seconds 6` after default scene load for full `UnloadScene` path).
4. For P4-managed projects, remind the user when edits touch already checked-out files.
5. Engine docs: `Active-Plan.md`, `Archived-Plan.md`, `EngineArchitecture.md`, `Docs/README.md` (**Active now**). Sync per `docs-roadmap-arch-sync.mdc` when policy/milestones change. **Task close:** collapse `_Progress.md` to **Closeout**, move Plan+Progress to **`Archived/plans/`**; move sprint line **Active-Plan** → **Archived-Plan**; at most **one** WIP pair at `Docs/` root.
6. Code comments in `VulkanDesktop/`: follow **`cpp-comments.mdc`**.
7. If implementation deviates from `{TaskName}_Plan.md`, apply the deviation protocol in the skill before continuing.
8. Render/descriptor work: follow **`vulkan-descriptor-per-draw.mdc`**; after S1 tasks, update **`Docs/Active-Plan.md` § S1 — implementation notes** if record/descriptor debt changed.
